# Warren Buffett Letters RAG Assistant

An intelligent question-answering system powered by Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) that enables users to interactively query nearly five decades of Warren Buffett's annual shareholder letters (1977–2024).

Instead of manually reading thousands of pages of investment wisdom, users can ask natural language questions and receive accurate, context-grounded answers drawn directly from the original letters.

---

## Project Description

The system ingests all publicly available Berkshire Hathaway shareholder letters, processes them into semantically meaningful chunks enriched with metadata (year, topic), and stores them in a vector database. When a user poses a question, the system retrieves the most relevant passages and uses a large language model to synthesize a coherent, cited answer.

A key feature is **temporal analysis**: since the corpus spans 47 years, the system can surface how Buffett's views on a given topic have evolved across decades — not just what he said, but *when* and *how* his perspective shifted.

---

## Motivation

Warren Buffett's shareholder letters are widely regarded as one of the most valuable free resources in finance and investing education. However, with nearly 50 years of letters totaling thousands of pages, finding specific insights on a particular topic (e.g., inflation, technology investing, risk management) requires significant manual effort. This project makes the entire corpus instantly searchable and queryable through natural language.

